name: AWS S3

options.name: s3_key_format
options.title: S3 Key Format
options.description: The format of keys in the S3 bucket for a corresponding dispatched file. May contain any of the following: 'service_id', 'service_ssd_id', 'service_name', 'process_id', 'process_name', 'process_execution_id', 'process_execution_started_at', 'process_execution_group_id', 'process_execution_group_count', 'process_execution_group_index', 'dispatching_service_name', 'output', 'output_name' or 'file_name'.

options.name: access_key_id
options.title: Access Key Id
options.description: The access key id part of the credentials, if credentials are provided.

options.name: secret_access_key
options.title: Secret Access Key
options.description: The secret access key part of the credentials, if credentials are provided.

options.name: session_token
options.title: Session Token
options.description: The session token part of the credentials, if credentials are provided and they use a session.

documentation_summary: This service dispatches to AWS S3.
documentation_description: You must provide the target bucket, and then optionally provide a custom S3 key format and AWS credentials.
